docs.abstract: At rallies, the president’s most fervent supporters look past his falsehoods, racially charged statements and attacks on critics. For his party to win Tuesday, he needs them to turn out in droves.
docs.snippet: At rallies, the president’s most fervent supporters look past his falsehoods, racially charged statements and attacks on critics. For his party to win Tuesday, he needs them to turn out in droves.
docs.lead_paragraph: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. — In two years, President Trump has reshaped the idea of America for his supporters. They repeat his tweets. They parrot what he says in speeches. Their views on taxes, immigration and the news media are, word-for-word, his views on taxes, immigration and the news media — as endlessly repeated by Fox News.

headline.main: Trump’s America: Aggrieved and Adoring Voices From Inside the Presidential Bubble
headline.print_headline: Voices From Inside the Presidential Bubble

docs.abstract: The case concerns a clash between a federal law that oversees uranium production and a state moratorium that by its terms addresses only extraction.
docs.snippet: The case concerns a clash between a federal law that oversees uranium production and a state moratorium that by its terms addresses only extraction.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When the largest known deposit of uranium in the United States was discovered in the 1970s in Pittsylvania County, Va., state lawmakers were wary. After some investigation, they imposed an indefinite moratorium on uranium mining.

headline.main: Justices Seem to Support Virginia’s Uranium Mining Ban
headline.print_headline: Justices Seem to Signal Support for Virginia’s Ban on Uranium Mining

docs.abstract: A letter forwarded to senators considering the nomination of Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh for the Supreme Court describes an episode at a party.
docs.snippet: A letter forwarded to senators considering the nomination of Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh for the Supreme Court describes an episode at a party.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A secretive letter shared with senators and federal investigators by the senior Democrat on the Senate Judiciary Committee charges that a teenage Brett M. Kavanaugh and a male friend trapped a teenage girl in a bedroom during a party and tried to assault her, according to three people familiar with the contents of the letter.

headline.main: Letter Claims Attempted Assault by a Teenage Brett Kavanaugh
headline.print_headline: Letter Accuses Kavanaugh of Attempted Assault While in Prep School

docs.lead_paragraph: Updated, Oct. 5, 2018: Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh cleared a major hurdle Friday morning in his quest for the Supreme Court, as the Senate voted narrowly to cut off debate on his nomination and move to a final vote as early as Saturday. Read the latest, here.

docs.abstract: Rules dating back to Jefferson are supposed to keep the Senate a decorous place where prerogative rises above partisanship. The Kavanaugh proceedings are breaking it.
docs.snippet: Rules dating back to Jefferson are supposed to keep the Senate a decorous place where prerogative rises above partisanship. The Kavanaugh proceedings are breaking it.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The nomination of Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh to the Supreme Court has exposed just how far the Senate has drifted from the rules of decorum that once elevated senatorial prerogative over party, leaving behind the kind of smash-mouth partisan politics that have long dominated the unruly House.

headline.main: Kavanaugh Proceedings Drive a Senate Once Governed by Decorum Into Rancor
headline.print_headline: Kavanaugh Hearing Shows Drift From Decorum

docs.abstract: The 203-to-32 vote showed Nancy Pelosi had most Democrats behind her, but the result kept alive the threat of a messy intraparty feud.
docs.snippet: The 203-to-32 vote showed Nancy Pelosi had most Democrats behind her, but the result kept alive the threat of a messy intraparty feud.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Nancy Pelosi overwhelmingly won the Democratic nomination on Wednesday to be speaker when the new Congress convenes in January, but the defection of 32 Democrats signaled that she could still face a divisive fight to lead the House just as the party assumes control.

headline.main: Pelosi Turns to Arm Twisting After Resounding Vote Leaves Her Just Short of Speakership
headline.print_headline: Win for Pelosi,  But Defections  Signal a Tussle

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump announced his intention late Saturday to quickly withdraw the United States from the North American Free Trade Agreement, a move intended to force House Democrats to enact a revised version of the pact despite concerns that it fails to protect American workers.

headline.main: Trump Says He Plans to Withdraw From Nafta
headline.print_headline: Trump Says He Intends To Withdraw From Nafta
